@AccountService @Postgres
Feature: Bank Account Management

  As a bank customer
  I want to create and retrieve savings accounts
  So that I can manage my finances securely

  Background:
    Given the bank account API is running
    And the offensive nicknames list contains "["badword1", "badword2"]"
    And the Maximum Number of Accounts Per Customer is "5"

  @Positive @Validation
  Scenario Outline: Successfully create a new savings account
    Given a customer with <CustomerNumber> already exists
    When I submit a request to create a savings account with <CustomerNumber>, <AccountNickName> and <BranchCode>
    Then the response status should be "201"
    And the response should contain an autogenerated account number
    And the account details should be saved in the database table
    And the customer should have not exceeded the maximum number of accounts per customer

    Examples:
      | CustomerNumber | AccountNickname | BranchCode |
      |          17990 | My Savings      |            |
      |           4091 |                 |            |

  @Negative @Validation
  Scenario Outline: Validate account creation input constraints
    When I submit a request to create a savings account with <CustomerNumber>, <AccountNickName> and <BranchCode>
    Then the response status should be "400"
    And the error message should be <ErrorMessage>

    Examples:
      | CustomerNumber | AccountNickname                 | BranchCode | ErrorMessage                                 |
      |                | ValidNick                       |            | Customer name is mandatory                   |
      | Alice          | Tiny                            |            | Nickname must be between 5 and 30 characters |
      | Bob            | ThisNicknameIsWayTooLongForBank |            | Nickname must be between 5 and 30 characters |
      | Charlie        | badword1                        |            | Nickname contains offensive content          |

  @BusinessRule
  Scenario: Prevent creation of more than 5 accounts per customer
    Given a customer with customer number "109212" already has 5 active accounts
    When I submit a request for customer number "109212" to create a new account
    Then the response status should be "409"

  @Positive
  Scenario: Retrieve an existing savings account
    Given a customer exists with customer number "17709"
    And they have "2" savings account
    When I request all the accounts that the customer holds
    Then the response status should be "200"
    And the response body should contain two account items

  @ErrorHandling @Database
  Scenario: Handle database unavailability
    Given the Postgres database is offline
    When I submit a request to create a savings account with <CustomerNumber>, <AccountNickName> and <BranchCode>
    Then the response status should be "500"
    
  Examples:
    | CustomerNumber | AccountNickname | BranchCode |
    |          17990 | My Savings      |            |
    |           4091 |                 |            |